{{Primarysource|date=February 2010}} '''Danubit''' is an industrial [[plastic explosive]] produced by the [[Slovakia|Slovak]] company [[Istrochem]]. It is intended primarily as a [[rock blasting]] explosive for surface and underground mass [[mining]] of mineral raw materials although underwater blasting applications are possible as well.
The producer of Danubit, [[Istrochem]], is a chemical company founded by [[Alfred Nobel]] in [[Bratislava]], [[Slovakia]].{{Fact|date=June 2009}}
