The '''Fürstenwalde Solar Park''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Fürstenwalde]], Germany.<ref>[http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx Large-Scale Photovoltaic Power Plants] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160101000000/http://www.pvresources.com/PVPowerPlants/Top50.aspx |date=January 1, 2016 }}</ref> It has a capacity of 39.64&nbsp;[[megawatt]] (MW) and an annual output of 36.5&nbsp;[[GWh]]. The solar park was developed by the company ''Solarhybrid'' and built by conecon using 62,832 225-watt and 110,880 230-watt [[solar panels]], both manufactured by Suntech.
The PV project was built on a former military airfield on {{convert|89|ha}}, and was completed in 10 weeks only.<ref>[http://www.pv-tech.org/news/work_begins_on_solarhybrids_40mw_fuerstenwalde_park Work begins on solarhybrid’s 40MW Fürstenwalde park]</ref><ref>[http://www.solarhybrid.ag/ref_fuerstenwalde.html?L=2 Fürstenwalde]</ref>
